CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 21, 1959, pg. 9, reads: "Presents Check - Gay DeHall, president of the D.I. Club of Pittsburgh, presents a check to Charles H. Bynum, national intergroup relations director for the National Foundation (March of Dimes0 at the glittering cabaret-fashion show held at the New Arena Supper Club, Sunday night. Mr. Bynum flew in from New York to accept the check in behalf of the Foundation. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of D. I. Club members Juanita Drake, and Gay DeHall wearing gold colored satin pants with mink tails on hem, standing on stage with Charles H. Bynum, in the New Arena Supper Club for D.I.'s "March" benefit for the National Foundation
